Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.00,0:00:26.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs100\t(,\fs110)\frz1\fad(3000,500)\fsp0\fscx120\pos(960,800)\b0\shad0\bord0}地          球          脉          动
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.50,0:00:33.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球的两极都被冰覆盖着\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Both poles of our planet are covered with ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.62,0:00:37.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是最大、最荒凉的无人区\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're the largest and most demanding wildernesses of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.46,0:00:45.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两极地区的季节变化非常极端\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Nowhere else on Earth is seasonal change so extreme.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.70,0:00:49.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使得冰盖面积每年都在扩大和缩小\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It causes the ice to advance and retreat every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.62,0:00:54.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里的一切生命都受其影响\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And all life here is governed by that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.22,0:01:04.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs140\fsp11.5\fad(1000,1000)\pos(966,950)}冰     封     世     界
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.25,0:01:12.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs60\fsp5\fad(1000,1000)\pos(960,1080)\bord0\shad3}画 外 音\N{\fs90}大卫 · 爱登堡   爵士
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.22,0:01:16.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,第一批极地探险家前往南方时候\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}When the first polar explorers headed south,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.14,0:01:21.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,经过这里的冰山就标志他们进入了未知领域\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}giant cathedrals of ice marked their entry into uncharted territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.78,0:01:28.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在经过高耸的冰山的时候\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Passing the towering spires,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.42,0:01:32.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们必曾感慨于地球上竟有如此别样的地方存在\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they must have wondered what unearthly sights lay in store.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.50,0:01:40.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们继续南上 触目皆是寒冰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As they battled on, the ice became increasingly dominant,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.46,0:01:49.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当冰雪世界真实的出现在他们眼前的时候 他们感到的是无法用语言形容的震撼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but nothing could have prepared them for the ice world that finally loomed into view.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.22,0:01:57.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里就是未知之地 拉丁语中的“Terra Incognita”！\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Terra incognita, ''the unknown land''.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.82,0:02:12.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,南极洲位于地球的最南边\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At the southernmost extreme of our planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.70,0:02:17.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,面积相当于一个美国\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the continent of Antarctica is as large as the United States of America.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.10,0:02:27.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里的冰占全世界的90%\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Ninety per cent of all the world's ice is found here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.14,0:02:34.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这个冰封的世界里大部分地方都死气沉沉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This frozen world is largely deserted
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.14,0:02:37.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直到春天来临\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}until the start of spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.30,0:02:43.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,阿德利企鹅\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Adelie penguins
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.02,0:02:45.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,行色匆匆\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}in a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.50,0:02:55.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,时钟滴嗒 时光飞逝\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The clock is ticking.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.78,0:03:00.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还没等到夏季解冻期的来临 这些鸟儿就急急忙忙从冰封的海洋赶到南极\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Instead of waiting for the summer melt, the new arrivals hasten south over the frozen sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.62,0:03:14.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们来这里繁衍\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They have come here to breed,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.70,0:03:16.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是极地的夏天是非常短暂的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but polar summers are so short,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.02,0:03:20.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,企鹅们必须赶在解冻期结束前做好就位的准备\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they must be in position before the thaw starts.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.10,0:03:27.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当海冰的面积缩小的时候\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As the sea ice retreats,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.94,0:03:32.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,动物便能长驱直入来到南极的腹地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}life can journey farther south.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.94,0:03:43.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,南极富饶的海水吸引着千里之外的客人来觅食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Antarctic waters are so rich that visitors come from far and wide to harvest them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.10,0:03:55.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,颊带企鹅成群结队地来到这里的岸边繁衍生息\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Vast numbers of chinstrap penguins come ashore to breed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.30,0:04:07.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,企鹅不会把蛋直接下在冰面上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}No bird will lay their eggs directly onto ice
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.34,0:04:11.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,于是裸岩就成了最重要的繁殖地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so bare rock is a vital commodity.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.78,0:04:14.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爬上最好的地方就算辛苦也是值得的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The best patches are worth the climb.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.66,0:04:22.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,数以万计的企鹅在此筑巢\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The cliff tops are soon stained pink
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.30,0:04:26.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们的粪便使山顶看起来一片粉红\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}with the droppings of tens of thousands of nesting penguins.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.90,0:04:38.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只有在几乎完全被冰覆盖的陆地上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}0nly in a land almost entirely covered in ice
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.82,0:04:41.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,裸岩才会被当作一块宝地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}could bare rock be reckoned an oasis.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.26,0:04:47.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为了找到裸岩一些企鹅会一直深入到南极中心\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Some will travel into the heart of the continent to find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.54,0:04:58.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些“冰原岛峰”下面是深埋在深达一英里的冰层里的庞大山脉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These are nunataks, the exposed peaks of vast mountain ranges buried in ice over a mile deep.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.42,0:05:05.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里静得可怕 只有到春天才会热闹起来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The eerie silence here is only broken in spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.58,0:05:17.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雪海燕来了 在这里求偶\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The snow petrels have arrived and are courting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.46,0:05:29.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,南极雪海燕的领地在地球的最南方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Antarctic petrels now join the most southerly bird colony on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.38,0:05:36.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们往内陆飞行300英里才来到这里繁衍\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The birds have flown inland for over 300 miles to reach this breeding site.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.70,0:05:43.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一旦小鸟破蛋而出\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}0nce their eggs have hatched,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.62,0:05:48.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雪海燕将为觅食而不断往返海陆600英里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they will be forced repeatedly to make the 600-mile round trip to gather food in the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.54,0:05:55.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过先得保护好来之不易的筑巢地 免得被其他鸟类占据\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}First, though, valuable nesting places must be defended from property thieves.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.58,0:06:08.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产蛋后雪海燕会在抽出时间在雪地里整理羽毛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}After laying their eggs, the petrels take time out to clean their plumage.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.58,0:06:34.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,南极贼鸥是可怕的机会主义者\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The south polar skua is a formidable opportunist.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.10,0:06:43.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是贼鸥碰到海燕并非机遇使然, 它们早就等着下手\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But the skuas have not chanced upon the petrels, they've been waiting for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.70,0:06:52.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,贼鸥不需要到海洋里捕食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These birds do not need to go to the ocean for their food.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.58,0:07:13.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,与其他猛禽相比 贼鸥的厉害在于它能在地球的最南端生存\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The skuas can survive further south than any other predator
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.94,0:07:18.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们知道利用海燕必定寻找裸岩筑巢的弱点\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}by exploiting the petrels' desperate need for bare rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.06,0:07:29.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在南极洲 即使是盛夏\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Even at the height of summer,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.74,0:07:33.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,南极洲也只有不到3％的地方没有被冰封\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}less than three per cent of Antarctica is free of ice,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.26,0:07:37.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几乎所有的裸岩都集中在同一个地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and nearly all of that exposed rock is found in one place,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.94,0:07:40.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即南极半岛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the Antarctic Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.98,0:07:53.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里与南极洲的其它地方相比更靠近北边, 所以春天先来到这里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Its long arm extends further north than the rest of the continent, so spring arrives here first.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.18,0:08:15.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,解冻后出现一些风平浪静的海湾 可以躲避南极洋无情的风浪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The thaw unlocks sheltered bays that provide refuge from the relentless battering of the Southern 0cean.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.10,0:08:23.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,水里有动静\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the depths, something stirs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.30,0:08:48.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,座头鲸！\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Humpback whales.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.22,0:08:53.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们经过5000英里的漫长旅程终于来到了这片水域\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They have travelled over 5,000 miles to reach these waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.18,0:09:03.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些鲸现在正美美地享受着磷虾大餐\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The whales are harvesting krill,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.22,0:09:08.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,冰层一融化各种各样的虾就会聚集在这里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}shrimp-like creatures that begin to swarm here as soon as the ice retreats.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.02,0:09:25.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,潜入到虾群中后\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Diving into the heart of the swarm,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.26,0:09:30.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,座头鲸会共同配合 紧密协作\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}teams of whales spiral round each other in close coordination.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.50,0:09:38.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在座头鲸转身 利用呼吸孔吐气 喷向猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Now they turn, blasting air from their blowholes, and ascend towards their prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.50,0:09:46.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,螺旋型的气泡网逐渐收紧,把磷虾聚在一起\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The krill becomes concentrated as the spiralling net of bubbles draws inwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.66,0:10:16.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,时光短暂,座头鲸昼夜不停捕食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The team of whales work round the clock for the boom is short-lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.30,0:10:20.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,短暂的夏天正逐渐消失\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Summer is already fading
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.26,0:10:24.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很快冬季又到了 这些鲸鱼将不得不前往北方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the whales will soon be forced north as winter returns.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.26,0:10:31.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳的威力逐渐减弱\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The sun's influence diminishes
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.70,0:10:33.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海洋开始结冰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the ocean starts to freeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.42,0:10:38.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们这个行星上最显著的季节变化正在发生\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The greatest seasonal change on our planet is underway.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.78,0:10:46.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,冰盖的面积以非凡的速度扩大\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The ice grows at an extraordinary rate,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.50,0:10:49.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一天扩大2.5英里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}advancing two and a half miles a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.18,0:10:53.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几个星期之内,整个南极大陆的面积将扩大为原来的两倍\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In a matter of weeks, the continent effectively doubles in size.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.30,0:11:00.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,生物纷纷逃离南极洲\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Life flees from Antarctica.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.18,0:11:09.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但偏有一种生物赶来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But one creature is just arriving.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.42,0:11:20.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,帝企鹅每年冬天便离开它们安逸的海洋家园\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Every winter, emperor penguins leave the comfort of their ocean home
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.26,0:11:23.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,开始了非凡的征途\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and begin a remarkable journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.02,0:11:30.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们要前往繁殖地,几乎在离海岸100英里的内陆\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They head towards their breeding grounds, almost 100 miles inland.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.98,0:11:57.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,帝企鹅将最终到达它们出生的故乡\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Eventually, the emperor penguins reach the place where they were hatched,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.50,0:12:01.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个位于冰封的洋面上、到处冰山林立的地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}an area sheltered by icebergs, trapped in the frozen ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.10,0:12:05.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这里 它们将繁衍下一代\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Here they will raise the next generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.42,0:12:15.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是 首先每只企鹅必须找到自己的配偶\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But first, each must find a mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.82,0:12:21.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雄企鹅开始唱情歌\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The males begin to serenade.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.82,0:12:31.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果有雌企鹅回应, 它们就结成一对,共同摆出雕像般的姿势\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And if a female replies, they pair up, posing like statues.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.38,0:12:38.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,新的企鹅对很快就会建立深厚的感情\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}New couples quickly form a strong bond.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.50,0:12:41.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们似乎对周围的喧嚣充耳不闻\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They seem oblivious to the noisy crowd around them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.74,0:12:49.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为了巩固它们的关系 雄企鹅跟雌企鹅走出行列\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}To cement their relationship, the male steps out with his female.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.10,0:13:03.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们的交配很短暂 不浪费一分钟\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The brief courtship complete, there isn't a moment to lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.22,0:13:06.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,求表现的压力太大\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With so much pressure to perform,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.90,0:13:09.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,任何雄企鹅都会拼命留在上面\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}any male would struggle to stay on top.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.74,0:13:17.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几周之后\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Several weeks later,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.30,0:13:21.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,绝大多数的企鹅对都会成功繁衍出下一代\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and it seems that most couplings were successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.62,0:13:26.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但体力也在产蛋的过程中消耗殆尽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But producing the egg has taken its toll.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.14,0:13:30.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雌企鹅再也没有孵蛋的力气\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The females no longer have the energy to incubate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.62,0:13:33.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,任务便交给了雄企鹅\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The male takes over.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.90,0:13:37.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,此时温度还是零下20摄氏度\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's still minus 20 degrees centigrade,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.90,0:13:39.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以交接过程必须迅速完成\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so the transfer must be done quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.66,0:13:41.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,否则蛋会冻坏\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}or else the egg will freeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.22,0:13:43.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有裸岩可以在上面筑巢\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With no bare rock to nest on,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.18,0:13:46.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雄企鹅会小心翼翼地把蛋藏在自己的体袋里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the male tucks the egg into a special pouch,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.74,0:13:48.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以让蛋保持足够的温度\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}where he can keep it warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.94,0:13:52.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,交接过程需要双方高度的配合\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It requires an extraordinary piece of teamwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.66,0:13:58.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在饥饿的驱使下\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Driven by hunger,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.86,0:14:02.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,精疲力竭的雌企鹅们独自返回海洋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the exhausted females now return to the ocean on their own,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.74,0:14:07.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,再次踏上了1月前曾和雄企鹅共同走过的漫漫征途\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}repeating the epic journey they made with the males only a month before.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.26,0:14:17.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在太阳只能勉强升到地平线上方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Now the sun barely appears above the horizon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.82,0:14:22.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着白昼的缩短,南极大陆变得越来越冷\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As the days shorten, its warmth is withdrawn from the continent.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.18,0:14:35.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雌企鹅去了之后\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With the females gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.90,0:14:39.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,企鹅的领地开始出现奇特的变化\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the colony undergoes a strange transformation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.78,0:14:46.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雄企鹅们聚集在一起,此时它们的蛋仍然藏在脚上面\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The males shuffle into groups, their eggs still tucked away above their feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.22,0:14:55.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们紧紧挤成包围圈以此取暖\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They lock together in tightly-packed huddles as they struggle to keep warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.34,0:15:03.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在快镜头下我们可以看到包围圈在不断地变动\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Speeding up the action reveals how these huddles constantly shift and change
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.50,0:15:07.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每只企鹅都要变换位置以进入更温暖的内部\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}as each penguin works its way towards the warmer interior.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.66,0:15:14.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些企鹅性情特别温和 这是环境使然\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Crammed into this scrum, the birds are remarkably good-natured. But they have to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.62,0:15:19.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果包围圈散了,哪怕就一小会儿 宝贵的热气也会消散\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}If the huddle breaks, even for a moment, precious heat escapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.22,0:15:41.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们必须尽最大的努力重新组成队列\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's imperative they reform as quickly as possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.42,0:15:43.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为只有团结成一体\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}for only by acting as one
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.46,0:15:49.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雄企鹅才能抵挡严酷的自然力量 才能保护好它们的蛋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}can the males withstand the elements and protect their eggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.50,0:15:56.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是最大的考验还在前头\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But their greatest test lies ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.94,0:16:01.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着隆冬的逼近,暴风雪越来越频繁 温度越来越低\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As winter advances, frequent blizzards drive the temperature down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.34,0:16:06.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在已经是零下60度\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's now 60 degrees below zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.82,0:16:14.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,处于边缘的企鹅承受着时速100英里的狂风袭击\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The birds at the edge of the huddle bear the brunt of the 100-mile-an-hour winds
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.22,0:16:18.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以便保护轮流站在中央的企鹅\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and so provide shelter to those taking their turn in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.06,0:16:31.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳已经完全消失,雄企鹅们与它们的蛋相依为命\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Abandoned by the sun, the males are left alone with their eggs
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.22,0:16:35.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来抵抗这地球上最寒冷、最黑暗的冬天\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to face the coldest, darkest winter on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.70,0:16:45.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而在地球的北极\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At the northern extreme of our planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.70,0:16:49.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳在数个月的沉寂后第一次升起\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the sun rises for the first time in months,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.58,0:16:53.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,阳光照亮了一个截然不同的冰的世界\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}illuminating a very different ice world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.62,0:16:57.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,与南极不同\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Unlike Antarctica,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.14,0:17:03.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,北极是广阔的冰封海洋 被陆地包围\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the Arctic is a vast frozen sea surrounded by land.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.26,0:17:07.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里的冬天已经临近尾声\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Here winter is coming to an end
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.30,0:17:12.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但这片荒凉的无人区仍然是冰封的天地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but this bleak wilderness remains locked in ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.22,0:17:22.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,绒鸭的到来打破了这里的平静\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Eider ducks break the silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.82,0:17:25.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,绒鸭没有迁徙到温暖的南方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They have stayed here, braving the northern winter,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.86,0:17:29.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而一直坚守在这里经受着北方寒冬的考验\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}instead of flying south to warmer climes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.34,0:17:38.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,4万只绒鸭飞越这一片冰天雪地的荒野\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Flocks 40,000 strong sweep across the frozen wastes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.06,0:17:54.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们都有相同的目标--冰间湖（冰穴）\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They all have the same goal, a polynya,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.86,0:18:01.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,冰间湖是结冰的海洋上永久性的洞孔 因为有强大的洋流使它们冬天也不会冰封\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}a permanent hole in the sea ice, kept open throughout the winter by strong ocean currents.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.42,0:18:10.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个不同寻常的水池是过夜的庇护所\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This unusual duck pond provides an overnight sanctuary
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.98,0:18:14.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且到了白天还有难得的进食机会\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and, when day breaks, a rare chance to feed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.66,0:18:29.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就在离冰面10米以下的海底上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Just 10 metres beneath the ice,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.10,0:18:32.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,布满了密密麻麻的贻贝\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the sea floor is carpeted with dense mussel beds.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.06,0:18:38.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个地方只有在洋流暂时停歇时才能吃到\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These can only be reached during a brief lull in the currents.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.70,0:18:44.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,绒鸭必须赶在潮流转向之前迅速采食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The ducks must quickly prise the mussels free before the tide starts to turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.26,0:18:53.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,机会之窗随时可能关闭\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The window of opportunity is short.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.38,0:18:58.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,洋流开始转强时它们就只好远走高飞了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As the current begins to build, it's up, up and away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.78,0:19:15.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个长年不冻的水窟窿提供了整整一个冬天的食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These permanent holes in the ice provide seafood throughout the winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.42,0:19:19.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其它生物也似乎闻风而来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The diners attract others.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.26,0:19:30.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在北极 每一处破冰的地方都是一条生命线\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the Arctic, any breach in the icy barrier can be a lifeline.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.10,0:19:37.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,麝牛创造了自己的生命线\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Musk oxen create their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.70,0:19:42.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种体型巨大的动物有足够的力量砸出冰窟窿\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These giants have the strength to smash through the frozen crust
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.34,0:19:44.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,再吃下面的植物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to graze on the vegetation below.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.74,0:19:54.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,麝牛破冰也为其它越冬的动物创造机会\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The ice-breakers create an opening for other over-winterers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.62,0:20:00.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,成群的雷鸟与麝牛结成了紧密的伙伴关系\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Flocks of ptarmigan make unusual grazing companions for the musk oxen,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.14,0:20:03.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们的活动忙碌一整天\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}whose entourage grows throughout the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.26,0:20:16.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些食草动物组成的奇特群落当然会引起注意\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This odd assembly of vegetarians doesn't go unnoticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.26,0:20:20.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一头北极狐\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}An arctic fox.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.42,0:20:27.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,麝牛最近生了幼仔\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The musk oxen have recently given birth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.62,0:20:32.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对于北极狐来说 这是一个捕食的机会\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For the fox, it's a chance to scavenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.26,0:20:44.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过在半数是脾气暴躁的母牛面前不好硬来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But half a ton of mad hairy cow is not to be trifled with.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.06,0:20:56.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,牛犊出生在春天冰盖融化之前\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The calves are born well before the spring melt,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.02,0:21:00.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样可以顺利地迎接夏天的到来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}giving them a head start when summer finally arrives.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.30,0:21:08.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们必须适应这个冰雪世界\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It must get to grips with its new ice world,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.22,0:21:12.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但天气喜怒无常\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}benign one minute, life-threatening the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.30,0:21:22.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即使是春天 仍然寒风彻骨\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Even in spring, winds chill to the bone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.82,0:21:30.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小牛必须紧跟着母亲 才能避免在突如其来的暴风雪中迷路\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The calf must stay close to its mother to avoid getting lost in the sudden blizzard.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.74,0:21:42.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,北极狼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Arctic wolves!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.30,0:21:50.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在白茫茫的天气中 有危险也几乎不可能察觉到\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the whiteout, the threat is almost impossible to detect,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.82,0:21:54.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是麝牛本能地向高地撤退\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but the musk oxen instinctively retreat to higher ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.14,0:22:16.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,成牛围成圈以保护它们的小牛, 一般的猎食动物很难突破这层封锁\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Forming a defensive ring around their calves, the adults present a barricade that few hunters could breach.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.26,0:22:22.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是今天的这头狼不需要冒受伤的危险硬闯\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But the wolves need not risk injury today.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.26,0:22:31.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们在慌乱之中留下一头小牛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A calf has been left behind in the panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.74,0:22:45.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着时间一天天过去,天上的太阳升得越来越高\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With each passing day, the sun climbs higher in the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.90,0:22:48.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,阳光逐渐直射到北极来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and its rays strike the Arctic more directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.26,0:22:53.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,新的生命在春天的气息中开始蠢蠢欲动\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's spring and new life stirs.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.26,0:23:02.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小北极熊从洞穴中探出头来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The polar bear cubs emerge from the den in which they were born.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.22,0:23:07.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们的母亲在雪下呆了5个月后终于可以出来伸伸腿\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their mother stretches her legs after five months under the snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.46,0:23:15.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小熊才两个月大\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They are just two months old
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.14,0:23:17.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,本能地跟在母亲后面\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and instinctively follow her lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.30,0:23:36.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,陡峭的斜坡是穴居的好地点\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A steep slope makes the best site for a den,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.02,0:23:40.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但第一次踏出脚时是不能掉以轻心的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but it's a tricky place to take your first steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.22,0:24:04.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能看起来很好玩, 但这都是为马上来临的严峻挑战所做的训练\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It may look like fun but this is serious training for the task ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.86,0:24:06.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,山坡上面没有食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There is no food on the slopes
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.66,0:24:12.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在母熊奶水干涸之前 一家人需要穿越冰封的海洋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the family will need to head out across the frozen sea before the mother's milk runs dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.38,0:24:21.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两周后它们做好了准备\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Two weeks later, they are ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.10,0:24:26.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雌熊有可能在海冰上捕食到海豹\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}0ut on the sea ice, the female can hunt for seals
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.54,0:24:30.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是这个冰雪世界危机四伏\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but it will take all her mothering skills to keep her cubs safe
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.90,0:24:34.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要保护好自己的幼仔 母熊必须施展出所有的本领\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}in this dangerous world of ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.74,0:24:52.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每年一次的解冻期来了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The annual melt has begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.38,0:24:57.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对于北极熊一家来说 这是一个极富挑战性的时刻\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is a challenging time for the bear family.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.94,0:25:03.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两只幼熊中往往会有一只无法在第一年存活下来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}0ne out of every two cubs do not survive their first year out on the ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.14,0:25:19.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着太阳的威力逐渐增强, 海冰仿佛有了自己的生命\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As the sun's influence increases, the sea ice seems to take on a life of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.22,0:25:30.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,融化了的冰川水从陆地上喷泻而出\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Glacial melt waters pour from the land, mingling with the sea
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.34,0:25:35.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,与海水交汇 加速了解冻\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and speeding up the thaw.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.98,0:25:46.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海洋在不断地变迁, 破裂的冰块在风和洋流的作用下不停地移动着\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The seascape is in constant flux as broken ice is moved on by winds and currents.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.78,0:26:00.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,冰面开始变薄 已经很难承受一只雄性北极熊的重量\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The ice is becoming too weak to support a male polar bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.66,0:26:10.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这只北极熊试图分散身体的重量\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He attempts to spread his weight,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.54,0:26:15.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是在冬天能够支撑它的冰面现在正迅速地解体\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but the ice that has supported him all winter is rapidly disintegrating.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.26,0:26:22.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每年的天气变暖时 北冰洋的冰就会减少\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Each year, as the climate warms, the Arctic holds less ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.22,0:26:25.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对于北极熊而言 这是一场灾难\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is a disaster for polar bears.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.02,0:26:31.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有坚实的冰作为平台, 北极熊就不能猎捕它们赖以生存的海豹\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Without its solid platform, they can't hunt the seals they need in order to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.42,0:26:41.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种巨大生物的前途很不乐观\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This may be a glimpse of the unstable future faced by this magnificent creature.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.18,0:27:18.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,冰融化的时候 海鸟返回到北冰洋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As the ice disappears, seabirds return to the high Arctic.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.62,0:27:30.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小海雀成千上万地飞来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Little auks arrive in their millions.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.34,0:27:37.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在一些人的眼里, 这些海雀是北极的企鹅\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In some ways, these birds are the penguins of the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.82,0:27:42.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们寻找裸岩 好在上面产蛋, 它们长得也有几分像企鹅\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They seek bare rock on which to lay their eggs and they look rather like penguins, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.78,0:27:54.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,与南极不同, 陆基的掠食动物也可以到达这里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Unlike Antarctica, the Arctic can be reached by land-based predators,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.90,0:27:57.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以小海雀仍然需要保持飞行能力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}which is why little auks have kept the ability to fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.50,0:28:05.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们利用岩肖山坡保护鸟蛋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They use scree slopes to protect their eggs,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.34,0:28:08.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,蛋藏在岩石下的深达1米的缝隙里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}burrowing up to a metre beneath the rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.22,0:28:18.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,盛夏的太阳从不落山\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At the height of summer, the sun never sets,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.46,0:28:22.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只是滑落在地平线上 再次升起\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but just skims the horizon before rising again.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.26,0:28:32.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,候鸟们从世界各地返回北极\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Migrants return to the Arctic from far and wide.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.02,0:28:38.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们来寻找美食和繁衍后代\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They've come to make the most of the brief flush of food and to produce their young.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.70,0:28:44.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沙丘鹤则从新墨西哥州一路赶到这里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Sandhill cranes have travelled all the way from New Mexico.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.50,0:28:55.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们的小鸟跟其他小鸟一起探索冻土地带\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their chicks join the growing band of youngsters exploring the tundra.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.90,0:29:04.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每年有几个月的时间\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For a few months each year,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.86,0:29:08.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,北极变成了所谓的“午夜太阳之地”\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the Arctic becomes ''The land of the midnight sun''
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.78,0:29:13.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一天24小时都是白昼 动物可以24小时觅食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and 24 hours of daylight allow animals to feed around the clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.38,0:29:19.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,北极狐终于有足够的食物来养活它的大家庭\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The arctic fox finally has enough food to raise her large family.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.26,0:29:39.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,选择了空旷地筑巢也就必须做好厮杀角逐的准备\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}If you choose to nest in the open, you must be prepared for a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.10,0:29:53.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,北极贼鸥会袭击任何侵犯它的领地的动物 甚至大型的草食动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Arctic skuas will see off any trespassers, even large vegetarians.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.22,0:30:45.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,冰雪世界最后在雄北极熊的脚下消失了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The male polar bear's ice world has finally vanished beneath him.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.62,0:31:00.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雌熊仍然在陆地上照顾小熊\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}While the female is still kept on land by her dependent cubs,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.74,0:31:04.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,公熊则来到大海里寻找食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the male can take to the sea in search of food. Ducking and diving,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.00,0:31:10.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,潜伏在水中准备袭击在残留的冰块上休息的海豹\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}he hopes to ambush seals resting on the remaining fragments of ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.90,0:31:42.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这个新环境里, 北极熊变成了一个身怀绝技的游泳高手\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In these new surroundings, he is a surprisingly adept swimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.70,0:32:00.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,曾经有人在离海岸60英里处发现了北极熊 这种事情是极难碰到的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}0nce an extremely rare sight, polar bears have recently been seen over 60 miles from the shore.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.58,0:32:18.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在已经没有回头路了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There is now no turning back for this bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.26,0:32:21.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它必须进入更深的水域\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He is forced to head out into deeper water.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.06,0:32:33.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它那巨大的前爪有力地拨动着海水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}His giant front paws help him to fight the ocean currents.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.26,0:32:57.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在海里它似乎是那样地悠游自在\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He seems at home in the sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.46,0:32:59.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是它不能永远游在水里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but he cannot swim indefinitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.98,0:33:08.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果在这片汪洋里一直找不到陆地它就会淹死\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He will drown if he doesn't find land somewhere in this vast ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.30,0:33:39.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海象正往低岛聚集\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Walruses are now gathering on low-lying islands.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.38,0:33:42.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们在海冰上产仔\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They gave birth on the sea ice,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.34,0:33:48.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但这块平台已经消失,它们需要新的地方哺育幼仔\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but with this platform now gone, they need a new place to haul out and nurse their young.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.82,0:33:55.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在海上漂流了几天之后公熊终于登陆了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}After several days at sea, the male bear finally makes landfall,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.02,0:34:00.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它已经嗅到了岛屿上散发出的强烈气味\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}drawn by the pungent smells emanating from the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.26,0:34:12.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但在夏天结束时,公熊的体重已经减少了一半\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}By the end of the summer, the bear has lost half his weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.22,0:34:18.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,冰层早已融化,迫使它到陆地上寻找食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With the ice long gone, he is forced onto land in search of food.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.46,0:34:30.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这座岛上找到吃的并不容易\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There will be no easy meals on this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.42,0:34:33.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海象是世界上最大的海豹科动物.\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Walruses are the largest seals in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.90,0:34:38.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,体重超过1吨,有长达1米的象牙为武器\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They weigh over a ton and are armed with tusks a metre long.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.74,0:34:45.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,游得精疲力竭的北极熊必须恢复体力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Exhausted from his swim, the bear must regain his strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.62,0:34:56.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,第二天海雾笼罩了这座岛屿\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The next day, a sea fog shrouds the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.58,0:34:59.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海象已经意识到危险\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The walruses sense that they are in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.54,0:35:07.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在海雾的掩护下,北极熊向海象群靠近\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Using the fog as cover, the bear approaches the herd.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.42,0:35:18.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但成象围成圈保护小象, 构成了一堵坚固的脂肪皮墙\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The adults close ranks around their young, presenting a wall of blubber and hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.78,0:35:29.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它先试探了一下但那里很坚固\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He tests the barrier, but it stands firm.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.54,0:35:36.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看起来这个世界上最大的陆地食肉动物遇到了对手\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It appears that the world's largest land carnivore has met his match.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.74,0:35:46.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一定在什么地方有破绽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There must be a chink in the armour somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.06,0:35:52.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不在这里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Not here!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.74,0:36:05.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雌海象在保护它的小象 如果能够把它拉开的话…\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This female walrus is shielding her pup, if he can just prise her off...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.30,0:36:17.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但熊的尖牙利爪都无法穿透海象厚实的毛皮\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The bear's claws and teeth can't penetrate her thick hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.26,0:36:30.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,象群开始往水里撤退,熊必须迅速出击\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With the herd retreating to water, the bear must move quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.06,0:36:38.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个失败后 它又径直奔向另一个\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Having failed with one, he heads straight for another.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.26,0:37:00.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,挨饿几个月后吃到第一顿饭的希望正变得越来越渺茫\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The chance of his first meal in months is slipping away.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.06,0:37:09.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看起来它变得越来越拼命\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He seems increasingly desperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.42,0:37:17.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是生死关头\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's now or never.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.74,0:37:21.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它必须躲开戳过来的象牙才能取胜\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He must avoid the stabbing tusks if he is to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.22,0:37:36.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但不断甩动身体的海象力气大得惊人, 它从浅滩被拖到海象群所在的安全地点\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The flailing walrus is immensely powerful and drags the bear away from the shallows towards the safety of the herd.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.62,0:37:54.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海象从北极熊的爪子下面逃走了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It slips from his grasp.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.38,0:38:07.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只有在盛夏 到了饿死的边缘\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}0nly at the height of summer,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.46,0:38:10.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,才会攻击这样危险的对象\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}when bears are on the verge of starvation, will they risk attacking such dangerous prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.74,0:38:19.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这只熊赌命一搏却输了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It was a gamble that this bear took and lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.42,0:38:28.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它受了重伤 现在连走路都很困难\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The stab wounds he received from the walrus are so severe that he can barely walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.26,0:38:35.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海象们恢复了平静\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The walruses are calm again,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.02,0:38:41.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,似乎意识到受伤的熊 再也不会对自己和幼仔构成威胁\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}seemingly aware that the injured bear no longer poses a threat to them or their young.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.34,0:39:01.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,找不到食物,这只熊将无法活下来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Unable to feed, this bear will not survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.38,0:39:16.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果全球气候继续变暖\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}If the global climate continues to warm,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.38,0:39:20.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,北极冰层融化的时间继续提前\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the Arctic ice melts sooner each year,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.98,0:39:23.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,肯定会有越来越多的熊遭受这样的命运\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}it is certain that more bears will share this fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.86,0:39:47.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在我们行星的最南方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At the southern end of our planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.06,0:39:51.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,火焰一样的极光照亮了冬季的夜空\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}fiery ribbons are illuminating the winter skies.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.18,0:39:54.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,南极光\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The aurora australis.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.34,0:40:02.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这道光并没有给还挤成一堆的雄企鹅带来温暖,\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This light brings no warmth to the male penguins,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.10,0:40:06.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们还挤在一起面对着地球上最严酷的挑战\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}who are still huddling, defying the coldest conditions on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.66,0:40:23.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但磨难已经接近尾声\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their ordeal is drawing to a close.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.30,0:40:37.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,南极洲的太阳在落山30天后 再次升起\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Thirty days after it last set, the sun rises once more on Antarctica.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.38,0:41:03.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们所经受的可怕考验就是为了这一刻\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their appalling trials have all been for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.34,0:41:23.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每个企鹅爸爸的嘴里都含着一口食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Each father has just one meal left inside him.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.42,0:41:26.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这口食物已经储存了整整一个冬天\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He has been saving it all winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.54,0:41:32.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就这一口吃的可以让小企鹅多存活几天\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This single feed will sustain the chicks for a few more days,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.06,0:41:36.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是雄企鹅已经四个月没有进食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but the males have not eaten for nearly four months.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.82,0:41:41.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果再不快点吃东西 它们和小企鹅都会死掉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}If they do not eat soon, they and their chicks will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.70,0:41:53.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是希望就在地平线那边\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But there is hope on the horizon.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.22,0:42:11.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雌企鹅们回来了,吃了一肚子的鱼回来了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The females are returning and their bellies are full with fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.58,0:42:22.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着它们脚步的临近, 雄企鹅们开始表现出抑制不住的兴奋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As they approach, waves of excitement ripple through the huddle.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.42,0:42:32.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雌企鹅们各自呼唤配偶\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Each female calls to her mate and he,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.54,0:42:37.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雄企鹅听到后就会大声回应\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}recognising her song, trumpets back.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.78,0:42:42.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,终于大团圆了！\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Reunited at last.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.30,0:42:49.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,企鹅妈妈第一次看到企鹅宝宝\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The mother sees her chick for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.50,0:42:56.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,便急不可待地想马上尽妈妈的责任\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She's keen to start parenting,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.42,0:43:00.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但整个冬天都在照顾小企鹅的爸爸倒是有点舍不得\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but the father needs persuading to surrender the chick he has been caring for all winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.50,0:43:12.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它现在要让小企鹅冒险, 在这种温度下 小企鹅随时有可能冻死\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He must now put his chick at risk. In these temperatures it could freeze in seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.26,0:43:17.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雄企鹅还是得放手\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The male will have to let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.22,0:43:29.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宝宝终于安全地交给了妈妈\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Eventually, the transfer to the mother is safely made.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.54,0:43:47.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小企鹅长得很快,吃小鱼和鱿鱼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The chicks grow quickly on a diet of fish and squid.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.62,0:44:04.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很快它们可以自由行动了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Soon they are keen to explore,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.22,0:44:06.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过妈妈总在旁边照看着\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but always with mother in tow.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.38,0:44:11.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是一只不幸的小企鹅\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This chick is less fortunate,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.70,0:44:14.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的妈妈没有来认养它\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}its mother has not returned to claim it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.02,0:44:19.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,另一只没妈妈的小企鹅在寻找新家庭\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Another orphan is searching for a new family,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.26,0:44:22.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但这只雌企鹅已经有了自己的宝宝\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but this female already has a chick of her own.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.30,0:44:37.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有些失去亲鸟的小企鹅受到了母鸟们过分的关注\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Some orphans receive too much mothering from penguins whose own chicks have not survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.26,0:44:43.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些母鸟们自己的宝宝夭折了 便争养任何碰到的孤儿\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The urge to parent is so strong that they will compete with one another to adopt any chick they find.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.58,0:44:52.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样的争来争去往往会以悲剧收尾\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Many of these squabbles end in tragedy
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.26,0:44:55.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可怜的小企鹅有可能被活活压死\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}as the poor chick is trampled to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.46,0:45:12.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而有父母的小企鹅很快就要学习生存的技能\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Those chicks that do have parents quickly learn survival skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.22,0:45:17.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即使在春天 小企鹅们也必须挤在一起\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Even in spring, they must huddle together for warmth,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.34,0:45:19.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像寒冬时节它们的爸爸做的那样\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}just as their fathers did in the depths of winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.50,0:45:27.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有一群小企鹅在暴风雪中迷路了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A group of chicks has got lost in the blizzard.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.50,0:45:38.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,迷失方向的它们在寒冷中四处寻找亲人\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Cold and disorientated, they search for the colony.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.90,0:45:49.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很快暴风雪中就会出现几具尸体\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It will not be long before the storm claims its first victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.26,0:46:12.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到了初夏 小企鹅已经发育得非常良好\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}By early summer, the chicks are surprisingly well-developed
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.74,0:46:15.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们已经做好了当上这个世界的主人的准备\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and now look ready to take on the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.06,0:46:22.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些在第一年里 存活下来的小企鹅有着最光明的前途\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Those that survive their first year have the best possible start in life
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.06,0:46:26.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,多亏了它们的爸爸和妈妈承受了非凡的考验\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}thanks to the extraordinary hardships endured by their parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.70,0:46:33.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在同南极的冬天抗争并取得了胜利\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Parents who battled with the Antarctic winter and won.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.02,0:46:47.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在北冰洋  两只小北极熊现在可以离开妈妈独立生活了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the Arctic, the two polar bear cubs are now independent of their mother
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.26,0:46:52.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,之前它们曾短暂地在陆地的家园团聚过\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and they briefly reunite where their home ranges overlap.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.66,0:47:01.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们在一起的时间很短\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their time together will be fleeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.66,0:47:04.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们一生的大部分时间都独来独往\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Most of their lives are now spent alone,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.70,0:47:08.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在冰封的海洋上四处游猎\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}wandering the vast tracts of frozen ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.34,0:47:38.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在跟它们母亲在一起的时候\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Following their mother
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.94,0:47:41.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们已经学会怎样生存在极地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}has prepared them for life at the pole,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.38,0:47:45.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这个永远在变的冰的国度\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}an ever-changing land ruled by ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.50,0:47:50.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们是否已经做好了适应更大的变化\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Whether they are ready for the bigger changes
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.38,0:47:56.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,适应已经开始影响这个冰雪世界的变化的准备, 还不得而知.\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that have begun to shape the ice worlds of our planet remains to be seen.

